To calculate Return on Assets (ROA), the formula is:

\[
\text{ROA} = \frac{\text{Net Profit}}{\text{Average Total Assets}} \times 100\%
\]

### Step 1: Identify Net Profit

From the income statement and cash flow statement, net profit is:

\[
\text{Net Profit} = 835,266.51
\]

### Step 2: Calculate Average Total Assets

\[
\text{Initial Total Assets} = 13,000,000.00
\]
\[
\text{Ending Total Assets} = 14,214,117.02
\]
\[
\text{Average Total Assets} = \frac{13,000,000.00 + 14,214,117.02}{2} = \frac{27,214,117.02}{2} = 13,607,058.51
\]

### Step 3: Calculate ROA

\[
\text{ROA} = \frac{835,266.51}{13,607,058.51} \times 100\% = 6.14\%
\]
